It's a romcom about a girl who just turned 16 (which is a legal marriage age in some parts of Japan) and some relatives who are revealed to be inugamis (dog gods) that she forgot about came over suddenly saying that the son is getting married to the girl and it was arranged during childhood, have fun with lots of laughter as the show is really funny

The above post is an accurate description. It's a typical "My conservative relatives prearranged a marriage for me without me even knowing about it" type of romcom. The reason it's good isn't necessarily because of the originality of the plot, but rather because it's executed well. Most of the characters are cute and lovable, with a couple even being iconic.

My main problem with the show is that the male lead (the guy engaged to the heroine) is EXTREMELY boring. He rarely says or does anything. I feel like the show could've been better if he was given a bit stronger of a personality. This isn't to say the show is bad, though. I definitely enjoyed it.
